The formula for a sphere's volume is [`V=\frac{4}{3}\pi r^3\text{,}`] where [`V`] is the volume and [`r`] is the radius. And [`\pi`] is a number that is about [`3.14\text{.}`] If we know the volume of a sphere is [`[$left]`] then we have the equation [`[$left]=[$right]\text{.}`] Is the radius [`[$proposed_solution]\text{?}`]

>> [@DataTable(
  [
    [PGML('[`[$left->TeX]`]'),
     PGML('[`=`]'),
     PGML('[`[$right->TeX]`]'),
    ],
    [PGML('[`[$lefteval->TeX]`]'),
     PGML('[`\wonder{=}`]'),
     PGML('[_]{$righteval}{3}'),
    ],
